## Section 5: User Roles

### NGO Administrator

The Administrator serves as the primary platform manager and oversees organisational operations.

Responsibilities include:

* Creating and managing projects
* Monitoring platform-wide activities
* Managing users and permissions
* Reviewing reports and analytics
* Monitoring transparency records
* Managing donor visibility and accountability information
* Overseeing organisation-wide performance metrics

### Project Coordinator

The Coordinator manages project execution and volunteer operations.

Responsibilities include:

* Managing assigned projects
* Assigning volunteers to projects
* Creating and managing project tasks
* Monitoring task progress
* Reviewing attendance submissions
* Updating project milestones and status
* Coordinating volunteer activities
* Responding to project issues and blocked tasks

### Volunteer

Volunteers contribute to projects and track their participation through the platform.

Responsibilities include:

* Completing assigned tasks
* Updating task status
* Logging attendance and hours worked
* Managing profile information
* Selecting skills and availability
* Viewing contribution summaries
* Tracking participation history and achievements

### Donor

Donors use the platform to monitor funded programmes and project outcomes.

Responsibilities include:

* Viewing funded projects
* Monitoring project progress
* Reviewing impact summaries
* Accessing programme health indicators
* Viewing donor reports
* Tracking outcomes of supported initiatives

